    <item>
      <title>Playstation Icons French version</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/399970</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">6f9a6725085edca433a5441c3cd2aea0225cdfa1</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 04 Sep 2022 08:34:51 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/63145cfe7118b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/63145d045cb84.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a translation of the Playstation UI mod in order to use it with the French version. I also hopefully corrected the washed out colors and changed the square and Triangle buttons to the japanese katakana characters ロ (Ro) and ハ (Ha) . I couldn't find a way to simply use the textures already included in this pack and it supported only a single character, so I did the best as I could. If you have a better solution, feel free to modify this and re-up the corrected pack ^^&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2 Choices:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Download the PACK version and simply replace your "permanent_2d_EuFrench.pack" .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Or get the MSBT version to get the raw files to put back in the .szs yourself &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;French version: Ceci est une traduction du mod pour UI Playstation deja existant pour la version FR. J'espere avoir corrigé les couleurs delavées de l'autre mod et j'ai aussi remplacé les icones pour carré et triangle par les caracteres japonais en Katakana ロ (Ro) and ハ (Ha) . Je n'ai pas trouvé le moyen d'utiliser les textures deja incluses dans le mod et ces parties de l'UI ne supportent qu'un seul caractere, donc j'ai fait de mon mieux. Si vous avez une meilleure solution, hesitez pas a editer ce pack et a le re-up ^^&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2 Solutions :&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;La version PACK ou il vous suffit de remplacer votre "permanent_2d_EuFrench.pack" .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;La version MSBT avec les fichiers decompressé a remettre vous meme dans les .szs.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/msbtwindwakerhdpsiconsfr.7z" type="application/x-7z-compressed"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/packwindwakerhdpsiconsfr.7z" type="application/x-7z-compressed"/>
      <category>User Interface</category>
      <category>User Interface</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Transparent Hero's Charm</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/382829</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">e071ab06ec765db7b4f3048de8953fe92a0199fe</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 10 Jun 2022 20:43:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/62a3acb22628b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/62a3acd733e32.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;As simple as it sounds, this mod makes the Hero's Charm Mask transparent so you can still see enemies' HP without looking all ugly and out of fashion.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;INSTALLATION&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Obiously, download the mod.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Extract the zip on its own folder or where you can find it. You will need this &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;yamu.dae&lt;/span&gt; file for later.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Open Switch Toolbox. If you don't have it, you can get it &lt;a href="https://github.com/KillzXGaming/Switch-Toolbox/releases/" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Locate your &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;permanent_3d.pack&lt;/span&gt;&#13;
 file. It should be in GAME FOLDER\content\Common\Pack. If you don't &#13;
know where your game folder is, you can open Cemu, right-click on the &#13;
game and select "Game directory".&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drag it into Toolbox. Expand the folder and you should see every file that it contains.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Double click on the file &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Link.szs&lt;/span&gt; to unpack it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Double click &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Link.bfres&lt;/span&gt; to unpack it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Expand the &lt;b&gt;Models&lt;/b&gt; folder. Locate the &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;yamu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; model, it's near the end.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Right click it and select &lt;b&gt;Replace&lt;/b&gt;. Remember the &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;yamu.dae&lt;/span&gt; file we extracted? Browse to it and select it.&lt;br&gt;A window will appear, don't touch anything and press &lt;b&gt;Ok&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;A second window will appear. De-select the &lt;b&gt;"Use material"&lt;/b&gt; box and press &lt;b&gt;Save&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Now, save everything with the save button in the top left corner.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;Done!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/wwhd_-_transparent_heros_charm.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Link</category>
      <category>Skins</category>
    </item>
